{
  "stem": "3380.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But people that complained that they don't feel good, they had to line up in lines.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "So I tried to-- to see that the-- that the people should stay in line.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And he was the doctor-- he was a real doctor-- and he was decided who should go out-- who can go out on a roll call, and who cannot.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the meantime, transports went away from Buchenwald to different camps.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one day-- I don't know how many days I was there-- I remember that I made arrangement that my brother should remain there in a special place, Sam, and he remained.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A transport went away, and they came in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "An SS man comes into the camp and he said that the-- he needs the doctor going to go with this in this transport, and the assistants will remain.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I became automatically a full doctor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And listen, I took it over, I mean, for the-- for the medication and for the health.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he didn't do anything, and I didn't do either.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was no medicine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was no aspirin, no-- absolutely nothing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, and I was doing his job.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He gave me-- he-- the SS man told me that I should put on a band, a Red Cross band, and I became the block-- block doctor.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So, listen, what can you do?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I became a title like this in no time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was there for maybe a week or two.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Other transports went away from Buchenwald to other camps where they needed help.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] An SS man comes in and takes me away and that I'm going to go with the transport as a doctor with this and this transport.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know what to say to him.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
